cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR 

The paper deals with person re-identification, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves deep learning techniques, which makes cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel model for part alignment, which involves multi-task learning and self-attention, indicating that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of mis-alignment, which could be considered a security issue, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a possible sub-category as well.
